===[[Pokémon Masters EX]]===
{{main|Hilbert (Masters)}}
Hilbert, who is based on the [[player character]] from {{game|Black and White|s|Pokémon Black}}, forms a [[sync pair]] with {{p|Oshawott}} and its evolved forms {{p|Dewott}} and {{p|Samurott}}, along with {{p|Mightyena}}, {{p|Genesect}}, {{p|Glaceon}}, {{form|Thundurus|Incarnate Forme}} {{p|Thundurus}}, and {{Shiny}} {{form|Kyurem|White}} {{p|Kyurem}} in [[Pokémon Masters EX]]. Hilbert became a playable sync pair on September 24, 2019.

In this game, his reason for looking for {{mas|N}} during the events of {{B2W2}} is revealed to be due to N having left too suddenly for Hilbert to say goodbye to him, which is similar to what Hilbert's mom also says in Black 2 and White 2. Hilbert first appeared as an NPC during the eighteenth chapter of the [[PML arc]]. He also made a notable appearance later in the [[villain arc]]. 

